Restaurant Golden River, is run by the Wong family. It’ s a typical traditional Chinese restaurant once seen in every village in the Netherlands. Already in the 1920‘s the first Chinese restaurants appeared in harbour cities like Rotterdam. After WW2, they become more popular due to the repatriation of Indonesian families who after the Indonesian indepence moved back to holland. Once the favourite family restaurant, big portion sizes and cheap prices. Now these restaurants are disappearing fast and are taken over by all you can eat sushi places and stir fry restaurants.

This month in National Geographic Nederland*Belgë;
Photo reportage 'Bij de Chinees' , a portrait of a typical Chinese restaurant in the Netherlands
